Metadata: Parasites of Dover sole, "Microstomus pacificus" (Lockington), from northern California
"Proceedings of the Helminthologicaâ€‹l Society of Washington," 54(1):111-114, 1987.

A total of 232 Dover sole ("Microstomus pacificus") from northern California were examined for parasites. Of these, 226 (97.4%) were infected with at least one kind of parasite. Seventeen species of parasites were recovered. Dover sole are new host records for 11 parasite taxa; 4 others are reported for the first time from California waters.
